  "title": "onStateChange does not receive page update from infinite hits",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\n\r\n<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Bug reproduction\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce the behavior:**\r\n\r\n1. Go to https://codesandbox.io/s/dark-river-27qdw?file=/src/app.js:229-242\r\n2. Click on \"show more\"\r\n4. See console.log onStateChange was called\r\n5. see that page did not change\r\n\r\n<!-- A live example helps a lot! Fork the sandbox, reproduce the bug and paste the URL here: -->\r\n\r\n**Live reproduction:**\r\n\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/s/dark-river-27qdw?file=/src/app.js:229-242\r\n\r\n## 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\n<!-- A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen. -->\r\n\r\npage should change, like it does when you don't use `onStateChange`\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<!-- If applicable, add screenshots to help explain your problem. -->\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n- Version: 4.4.0\r\n\r\n## Additional context\r\n\r\n<!-- Add any other context about the problem here. -->\r\n",
